# Power BI Dashboard
An interactive dashboard was built in Power BI to analyze and compare the performance of Control and Test campaigns.

# Data Modeling
- Combined datasets using Power Query (Append)
- Created a unified table with a "Group" column (Control vs Test)
- Cleaned and transformed data for analysis

# DAX Measures Created

The following DAX measures were created to evaluate A/B test performance
Total Purchases = SUM(Append1[Purchase])

Total Clicks = SUM(Append1[Website Clicks])

Total Spend = SUM(Append1[Spend_USD])

Conversion Rate (CR) = 
DIVIDE([Total Purchases], [Total Clicks])

Cost Per Acquisition (CPA) = 
DIVIDE([Total Spend], [Total Purchases])

# Visualizations

The dashboard includes:

- KPI Cards:
  - Conversion Rate (CR)
  - Cost Per Acquisition (CPA)
  - Total Purchases
  - Total Spend

- Comparison Table:
  - Side-by-side comparison of Control vs Test

- Bar Charts:
  - Purchases by Group
  - CR by Group
  - CPA by Group

- Trend Analysis:
  - Performance over time (Date vs Purchases/CR)

- Slicers:
  - Group filter
  - Date filter

# Key Insight

The Control group outperforms the Test group with:
- Higher conversion rate
- Lower cost per acquisition
Although the Test group generated more purchases, it required higher spend, making it less efficient.

# Conclusion
The dashboard clearly demonstrates that the Control campaign is more cost-effective and delivers better overall performance, making it the recommended strategy.

